{
  "stem": "12612.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they instructed the men to pile up the dead bodies and half-dead bodies like logs and make-- what do you call them, pyres?",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Flames?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Like-- like a bonfire, a human bonfire.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And while the Nazis were busy loading up the people on the train, some of the men decided that they're going to eat the livers of the people they were burning.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because that was the first food that they-- who knew what was going to be?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You know, you're going to be going on the train to be gassed, so here was a chance to eat something.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So we were-- it was our turn to go on the trains to be gassed.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And miracle of miracles, there were bombs overhead.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the-- the Nazis came running out of the train.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And when they saw that the Nazis were running, they stopped bombing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were-- some people were screaming that we should head for the hills, which were right around the tracks, to hide our faces in the sand and lay flat against the sand hills.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that in case the bombs do come, either they would miss us, or I don't know for what reason they told us to do it.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my mother said that we tried to make-- I don't remember if she said from potatoes or potato starch that the Nazis left on the [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] trains-- that they tried to make fires and tried to cook that.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But the last Nazis, as they were running off the plane, kicked over everything, so we couldn't eat it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Then we went to-- I don't know which soldiers came to help us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But we were sent to a little village called Trobitz.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the people there were crying.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
